reg_info.full_title: R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 593: EXEMPTION FROM SUBSECTION 85 (1) OF THE ACT - PROVINCE OF ALBERTA
reg_info.reg_name_text: EXEMPTION FROM SUBSECTION 85 (1) OF THE ACT — PROVINCE OF ALBERTA
reg_info.citation: R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 593: EXEMPTION FROM SUBSECTION 85 (1) OF THE ACT - PROVINCE OF ALBERTA
reg_info.act_under: Highway Traffic Act   Code de la route

content.content: 1. Alberta is designated as a reciprocating province and a bus inspected in the Province of Alberta is prescribed as a class of vehicle for the purposes of subsection 85 (2) of the Act. R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 593, s. 1.
